text.__SUMMARY__: Banksia mucronulata, commonly known as swordfish dryandra, is a shrub endemic to Western Australia. It was known as Dryandra mucronulata until 2007, when all Dryandra species were transferred to Banksia by Austin Mast and Kevin Thiele.
